commitResults.messageBody:
Add Increment: Level-0

Implement an initial skeletal version of the Duke that simply greets
the user and exits.
Echo input line by line, exiting at EOF.
The bye command terminates input reading. A farewell message is printed and the program exits.

Each line is stored and echoed as an acknowledgement.

The list command lists all stored tasks by printing each on a new line,
prefixed with the 1-based index.

commitResults.messageTitle: Use class to represent task entries
commitResults.messageBody:
Instead of String, use specialised class to represent task.

This is for further inclusion of non-trivial properties into the task
objects, such as status and longer description, etc.

Add the ability to store the status of a task and mark a task as
finished.

Also make the string representation of tasks include the done status
information.
Correct several mistakes in coding style.
